ipfixMIB.description: The IPFIX MIB defines managed objects for IP flow information export. These objects provide information about managed nodes supporting IP flow information export, including flow information export capabilities, configuration and statistics. They also allow to configure IP flow information export concerning the IP interface at which flow information is gathered, the flow selections methods used, and the collector to which flow information is exported. PsampMethodAvailability.name: PsampMethodAvailability
PsampMethodAvailability.description: Used to report the availability of a selection method: available(1) - the method is supported and can be used notAvailable(2) - the method is not available

ipfixCollectorTable.name: ipfixCollectorTable
ipfixCollectorTable.description: This table lists collectors to which reports are exported.

ipfixCollectorEntry.name: ipfixCollectorEntry
ipfixCollectorEntry.description: Defines an entry in the ipfixCollectorTable.

ipfixCollectorIndex.name: ipfixCollectorIndex
ipfixCollectorIndex.description: The locally arbitrary, but unique identifier of a collector. The value is expected to remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ipfixCollectorDstIpAddressType.name: ipfixCollectorDstIpAddressType
ipfixCollectorDstIpAddressType.description: The IP address type of the collector.

ipfixCollectorDstIpAddress.name: ipfixCollectorDstIpAddress
ipfixCollectorDstIpAddress.description: The IP address of the collector.

ipfixCollectorDstProtocol.name: ipfixCollectorDstProtocol
ipfixCollectorDstProtocol.description: The transport protocol used for exporting sampled packets to the collector. The recommended protocols are TCP (6), UDP (17) and SCTP (132). The default is SCTP.

ipfixCollectorDstPort.name: ipfixCollectorDstPort
ipfixCollectorDstPort.description: The port number of the collector.

ipfixCollectorReportsSent.name: ipfixCollectorReportsSent
ipfixCollectorReportsSent.description: The number of reports sent to the collector.

ipfixCollectorGroupTable.name: ipfixCollectorGroupTable
ipfixCollectorGroupTable.description: This table lists groups of collectors to which flow records packets are exported. If flow records are exported to only one collector the group consists of exactly one collector.

ipfixCollectorGroupEntry.name: ipfixCollectorGroupEntry
ipfixCollectorGroupEntry.description: Defines an entry in the ipfixCollectorGroupTable.

ipfixCollectorGroupIndex.name: ipfixCollectorGroupIndex
ipfixCollectorGroupIndex.description: The locally arbitrary, but unique identifier of a collector group. The value is expected to remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ipfixTemplateTable.name: ipfixTemplateTable
ipfixTemplateTable.description: This table lists templates used by the exporter.

ipfixTemplateEntry.name: ipfixTemplateEntry
ipfixTemplateEntry.description: Defines an entry in the ipfixTemplateTable.

ipfixTemplateId.name: ipfixTemplateId
ipfixTemplateId.description: The unique identifier for the template.

ipfixTemplateIndex.name: ipfixTemplateIndex
ipfixTemplateIndex.description: The locally arbitrary, but unique identifier of a field Id in the template identified by ipfixTemplateId. The value is expected to remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ipfixTemplateFieldId.name: ipfixTemplateFieldId
ipfixTemplateFieldId.description: The Field Id at position ipfixTemplateIndex in the template ipfixTemplateId. This implicitly gives the data type and state values that are exported.

ipfixTemplateFieldLength.name: ipfixTemplateFieldLength
ipfixTemplateFieldLength.description: The Length of the Field. Used to indicate if reduced encoding or variable length field is used.

ipfixObservationDomainTable.name: ipfixObservationDomainTable
ipfixObservationDomainTable.description: This table lists the Observation Domains used at the managed node.

ipfixObservationDomainEntry.name: ipfixObservationDomainEntry
ipfixObservationDomainEntry.description: Defines an entry in the ipfixObservationDomainTable.

ipfixObservationDomainId.name: ipfixObservationDomainId
ipfixObservationDomainId.description: The locally arbitrary, but unique identifier of an Observation Domain. The value is expected to remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ipfixInstanceObservationPoint.name: ipfixInstanceObservationPoint
ipfixInstanceObservationPoint.description: The point where the packet is observed. If it is e.g, an interface it points to the mib-II object of the interface.

ipfixInstanceStartTime.name: ipfixInstanceStartTime
ipfixInstanceStartTime.description: The date and time when exporting for this parameter set should start.

ipfixInstanceStopTime.name: ipfixInstanceStopTime
ipfixInstanceStopTime.description: The date and time when exporting for this parameter set should stop.

ipfixInstanceTable.name: ipfixInstanceTable
ipfixInstanceTable.description: This table lists active instances of packet sampling at the managed node.

ipfixInstanceEntry.name: ipfixInstanceEntry
ipfixInstanceEntry.description: Defines an entry in the ipfixInstanceTable.

ipfixInstanceIndex.name: ipfixInstanceIndex
ipfixInstanceIndex.description: The locally arbitrary, but unique identifier of an instance. The value is expected to remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ipfixInstanceTemplateId.name: ipfixInstanceTemplateId
ipfixInstanceTemplateId.description: The Id of a template in the template table. This implies the knowledge about the method chain from the method chain table. Furthermore it links the instance, method chain (selector) and template together. The identified template is applied to the stream of filtered/sampled packets observed after applying the method chain at the observation point.

ipfixInstanceCollectorGroupIndex.name: ipfixInstanceCollectorGroupIndex
ipfixInstanceCollectorGroupIndex.description: The index of the collector group to which packet reports are sent.

ipfixInstancePacketsObserved.name: ipfixInstancePacketsObserved
ipfixInstancePacketsObserved.description: The number of packets observed at the observation point.

ipfixInstancePacketsDropped.name: ipfixInstancePacketsDropped
ipfixInstancePacketsDropped.description: The number of packets dropped while filtering/sampling packets.

ipfixInstanceProcessId.name: ipfixInstanceProcessId
ipfixInstanceProcessId.description: The process id of the metering process used by this instance.

ipfixInstanceReportingProcessId.name: ipfixInstanceReportingProcessId
ipfixInstanceReportingProcessId.description: The process id of the reporting process used by this instance.

ipfixInstanceReportsSent.name: ipfixInstanceReportsSent
ipfixInstanceReportsSent.description: The number of reports on sampled packets sent to the collector.

ipfixMethodChainTable.name: ipfixMethodChainTable
ipfixMethodChainTable.description: This table contains method chains lists and connects them to the instances where they are applied to different observation points. The filtered/sampled packets are then exported.

ipfixMethodChainEntry.name: ipfixMethodChainEntry
ipfixMethodChainEntry.description: Defines an entry in the ipfixMethodChainTable.

ipfixMethodChainIndex.name: ipfixMethodChainIndex
ipfixMethodChainIndex.description: The locally arbitrary, but unique identifier of a template. The value is expected to remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ipfixMethodChainMethod.name: ipfixMethodChainMethod
ipfixMethodChainMethod.description: The method used for the template at a certain position in the method chain.

ipfixMethodChainPacketsObserved.name: ipfixMethodChainPacketsObserved
ipfixMethodChainPacketsObserved.description: The number of packets observed at the method entry point.

ipfixMethodChainPacketsDropped.name: ipfixMethodChainPacketsDropped
ipfixMethodChainPacketsDropped.description: The number of packets dropped while selecting packets.

ipfixCompliance.name: ipfixCompliance
ipfixCompliance.description: An implementation that complies to this module must implement the objects defined in the mandatory groups ipfixGroupMetering and ipfixGroupReporting. The implementation of all other objects depends on the implementation of the corresponding functionality in the equipment.

ipfixGroupMetering.name: ipfixGroupMetering
ipfixGroupMetering.description: All objects that are basic for the metering process. It contains a basic metering function (ipfixSelectAll), The template definitions needed for the export of data, the method chain that fixes the metering functions applied to the observation point and several parameters concering the export process and the collectors.

ipfixGroupReporting.name: ipfixGroupReporting
ipfixGroupReporting.description: These objects define the collectors i.e., the destinations of the exporting process.

ipfixGroupStatistics.name: ipfixGroupStatistics
ipfixGroupStatistics.description: These objects contain statistical values gathered at different points in the metering process.
